  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve Basic Education for 500 Zambian Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Community school of Katulumba, in the underprivileged Fishing Camp compound of Siavonga, Zambia, has 3 classrooms and 8 latrines for 500 students; Guardavanti plans to build 4 more classrooms and 18 more latrines, allowing proper education and improving sanitary conditions of attending students. Moreover, the school will be able to accept all the kids of the compound currently excluded from schooling due to lack of space. The funds requested cover the first half of the project&apos;s structures.</narrative>
  </description>
